# Plan Before Substantial Artifacts

STOP before generating a substantial new artifact — a new feature, a new doc/ADR/design, a new image, or any net-new file that represents real design work. Do NOT write it yet. First, in order:

1. Switch to plan mode (`SwitchMode` → `plan`).
2. Run the `/grill-with-docs` skill to stress-test the design and capture the glossary/ADRs as we go.
3. Only after the plan is agreed, generate the artifact.

If you catch yourself about to create such a file without having done the above, stop and do it now.

Exempt — proceed normally, no ceremony: trivial edits to existing files (small fixes, renames, formatting, one-line changes).
